Ing '''kasuba''', '''katsumba''' o '''cachumba''' ('''''Carthamus tinctorius''''' [[Carl Linnaeus|L.]]<ref>[http://www.bioversityinternational.org/fileadmin/bioversity/publications/pdfs/498.pdf Safflower - ''Carthamus tinctorius'' L<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>) (Sanskrit: कसुम्भ|[[IAST]]: {{lang|sa|kusumbha}}), a ''safflower'' king Ingles, metung yang tanaman a dakal sanga, mala-yerba (''herbaceous'') ampong , [[banwahan]] (''annual''). Tatanam de para king kayung laru o larung gule (''vegetable oil'') a makukwa kareng kayang butul. Maki tas lang {{convert|30|to|150|cm|in|abbr=on}} deng tanaman, at atin yang mabilug a buntuk sampaga, tall with (''globular flower heads''), at maki kule lang dilo, kahel o kule dalandan, ampong malutu deng kayang sampaga. Maki metung ya anggang limang buntuk sampaga ing balang sanga, a maki 15 anggang 20ng bini o butul balang buntuk. Katutubu ya ing kasuba kareng malanging kapatulugan Safflower is native to (''arid environments'') a pana-panaun mung mikaka uran. Atin yang malalam a yamut a [[taproot]], at uli na niti, kapad no reng kapatulugan a anti kaniti.

